==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foursome
<hw>Four"some</hw> <pr>(f⟦omac⟧r"s⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Four</ets> + 2d <ets>-some</ets>.]</ety> <def>Consisting of
four; requiring four participants.</def> <mark>[Scot. or
Golf]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foursome</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Foursome
<hw>Four"some</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Golf)</fld> <def>A
game between four players, with two on each side and each side playing
but one ball, the partners striking alternately. It is called a
<ecol><b>mixed foursome</b></ecol> when each side consists of a man and
a woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A group of four people or objects; <as>as, we need
another player to make a <ex>foursome</ex> for bridge</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>four-spot</ent>⟦br⟧
